AUDIO: '8 GB of VRAM. A few years ago, you probably wouldn\'t have associated that with AI video editing, but recently a very interesting model appeared, Bernini R. It runs locally and even makes video editing possible on ordinary GPUs.'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Today, I\'ll show you how to install it, how to use it, where things are most likely to fail, and how to edit videos without running out of VRAM. Let\'s begin. Hello, welcome to Smart Vision.'

